  <compounddef id="TRIM" kind="page">
    <compoundname>TRIM</compoundname>
    <title>TRIM$ Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">TRIM$(string-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Removes all leading and trailing spaces from the string expression and returns the result.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="TRIM_1autotoc_md671">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>TRIM$(&quot;<sp/><sp/><sp/>Hello<sp/><sp/><sp/>&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;Hello&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Normalise<sp/>user<sp/>input</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">input$<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;<sp/><sp/><sp/>command<sp/><sp/><sp/>&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;[&quot;;<sp/>TRIM$(input$);<sp/>&quot;]&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>[command]</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="TRIM_1autotoc_md673">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Only space characters (<computeroutput>CHR$(32)</computeroutput>) are removed; tabs and other whitespace are not affected.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the string has no leading or trailing spaces, it is returned unchanged.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>For trimming only one side: use <ref refid="LTRIM" kindref="compound">LTRIM$</ref> or <ref refid="RTRIM" kindref="compound">RTRIM$</ref>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
